<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFFA6827459A34F4B937FDB0" pageId="15" pageNumber="298" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFA6827459A34F4B937FDB0" blockId="15.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="15" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFA6827459A34F4BB40FD94" bold="true" box="[199,315,511,537]" pageId="15" pageNumber="298">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFFA6827441F34F4B877FD94" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="1990" box="[322,524,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yabbura">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFA6827441F34F4B877FD94" box="[322,524,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="298">Ecnomus yabbura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously recorded from many sites in the NT and northern WA (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFFA6827407C34F4BAA8FDB0" author="Cartwright, D. I." pageId="15" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref14543" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (1990) The Australian species of Ecnomus McLachlan (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 51, 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j / mmv. 1990.51.01" type="journal article" year="1990">Cartwright 1990</bibRefCitation>
). The species is recorded from a further eleven NT sites.
</paragraph>
